Portuguese Prime Minister Visits Shanghai 
Portuguese Prime Minister Antonio Guterres arrived in Shanghai from
Chongqing today as part of his five-day official tour to China.
He toured a financial and trade development zone in the Pudong New Area
and expressed interest in the area's economic and social developments
in the eight years it has been open.
He also attended an opening ceremony of a representative office of a
Portuguese bank.
Chen Liangyu, Shanghai's vice-mayor, met with Guterres this evening and
both expressed an interest in further expanding economic and trade ties
between Shanghai and Portugal.
